{"questionId":"12240","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">Consider the matrix <strong><em>A&nbsp;</em></strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {{{\\text{e}}^x}}&amp;{{{\\text{e}}^{ - x}}} \\\\   {2 + {{\\text{e}}^x}}&amp;1  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mtext>e</mtext>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                </msup>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mtext>e</mtext>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mo>−</mo>\n                    <mi>x</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <msup>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mtext>e</mtext>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mi>x</mi>\n                </msup>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p class=\"question\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">Find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> for which <strong><em>A</em> </strong>is singular.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>finding det<strong> <em>A </em></strong>=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^x} - {{\\text{e}}^{ - x}}\\left( {2 + {{\\text{e}}^x}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>e</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> or equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><em>A</em></strong> is singular ⇒&nbsp;det <strong><em>A</em></strong> = 0&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(R1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^x} - {{\\text{e}}^{ - x}}\\left( {2 + {{\\text{e}}^x}} \\right) = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>e</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^{2x}} - {{\\text{e}}^x} - 2 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>solving for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^x}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^x}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> &gt; 0&nbsp;&nbsp;(or equivalent explanation)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(R1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^x} = 2\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = \">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span> ln 2&nbsp; (only)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; &nbsp;N0</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12240","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.28","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Consider the matrix A = ( e x e − x 2 + e x 1 ) , where x ∈ R . Find the value of x for which A is singular.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"28","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}